{
  "title": "graph2otel / Self-Observability",
  "uid": "graph2otel-self-obs",
  "description": "Exporter-process health: per-collector scrape success/duration/staleness, build info, license-tier detection, checkpoint/watermark lag, and export-job throughput. Not tenant data — see the Entra/Intune dashboards for that.",
  "editable": true,
  "tags": ["graph2otel", "self-observability"],
  "timezone": "",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "1m",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-6h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "datasource",
        "label": "Datasource",
        "type": "datasource",
        "query": "prometheus",
        "current": {},
        "hide": 0
      },
      {
        "name": "tenant",
        "label": "Tenant",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "prometheus",
          "uid": "$datasource"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(graph2otel_scrape_success, tenant_id)",
          "refId": "tenant"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "multi": true,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        },
        "sort": 1
      },
      {
        "name": "collector",
        "label": "Collector",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "type": "prometheus",
          "uid": "$datasource"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(graph2otel_scrape_success{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}, collector)",
          "refId": "collector"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "multi": true,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "current": {
          "text": "All",
          "value": "$__all"
        },
        "sort": 1
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Metric naming caveat",
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "graph2otel emits **OTLP** metrics; Grafana Cloud ingests them into Mimir/Prometheus, which normalizes names: dots become underscores, and OTEL unit/type suffix rules may append `_total` (counters), `_seconds`, etc. — e.g. `graph2otel.scrape.staleness` → `graph2otel_scrape_staleness`, `graph2otel.scrape.errors` → `graph2otel_scrape_errors_total`. This dashboard is built against that underscored convention, but exact normalization depends on your OTLP→Prometheus pipeline config (some preserve original names or omit `_total`) — adjust queries if your metric names differ."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Collector health",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 4 }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Scrape success by collector",
      "description": "graph2otel_scrape_success{collector,tenant_id} — 1 = last scrape succeeded, 0 = failed.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 5 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "min": 0,
          "max": 1,
          "unit": "none"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["lastNotNull"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_scrape_success{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{collector}} ({{tenant_id}})"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "heatmap",
      "title": "Scrape duration",
      "description": "graph2otel_scrape_duration{collector,tenant_id} seconds.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 5 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "s" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "calculate": false,
        "color": { "mode": "scheme", "scheme": "Spectral" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_scrape_duration{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{collector}} ({{tenant_id}})",
          "format": "heatmap"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "type": "table",
      "title": "Scrape staleness (all collectors, sorted worst-first)",
      "description": "graph2otel_scrape_staleness{collector,tenant_id} seconds since last successful scrape. Sorted descending — top rows are the most stale.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 13 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "s" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "sortBy": [{ "displayName": "Value", "desc": true }]
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_scrape_staleness{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\"}",
          "format": "table",
          "instant": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Scrape errors by error type",
      "description": "graph2otel_scrape_errors_total{collector,tenant_id,error_type} — rate of errors, broken down by error.type.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 13 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["sum"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum by (collector, error_type) (rate(graph2otel_scrape_errors_total{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{collector}} / {{error_type}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Build & deployment",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 21 }
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Build info (what's deployed)",
      "description": "graph2otel_build_info{version,go_version} — constant 1-valued gauge, labels carry the deployed version.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 22 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "none" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": { "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": true },
        "textMode": "name",
        "colorMode": "none",
        "graphMode": "none"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_build_info{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{version}} (go {{go_version}}) — {{tenant_id}}",
          "format": "table",
          "instant": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "License tier",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 26 }
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "type": "table",
      "title": "Detected license tier by tenant",
      "description": "graph2otel_tenant_license_tier{tenant_id,tier} — which Entra/Intune license tier was auto-detected per tenant, so operators can see at a glance which collectors run in degraded/skipped mode (e.g. P2-gated risk/PIM collectors, license-gated Intune features).",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 27 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "none" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_tenant_license_tier{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "format": "table",
          "instant": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Checkpoint & watermark lag",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 33 }
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Checkpoint persist errors",
      "description": "graph2otel_checkpoint_persist_errors_total{collector,tenant_id} — failures writing the checkpoint file. A rising count means a collector risks re-processing or dropping events across a restart.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 34 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["sum"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum by (collector) (rate(graph2otel_checkpoint_persist_errors{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{collector}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "type": "table",
      "title": "Window-collector staleness (watermark lag)",
      "description": "Same graph2otel_scrape_staleness metric, pre-filtered to the log-shaped WindowCollectors (sign-ins, directory audit, provisioning, risk detections/risky users, Intune audit events) so watermark lag is visible separately from snapshot collectors. Adjust the regex if collector names differ from this heuristic.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 34 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "s" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "sortBy": [{ "displayName": "Value", "desc": true }]
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_scrape_staleness{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\", collector=~\"$collector\", collector=~\".*(signin|audit|provisioning|risk).*\"}",
          "format": "table",
          "instant": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Export jobs & cardinality guard",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 41 }
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Export jobs by result",
      "description": "graph2otel_export_jobs_total{report_name,result,tenant_id} — Intune reports-export job outcomes (succeeded/failed/timed out).",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 42 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["sum"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum by (report_name, result) (rate(graph2otel_export_jobs{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}[15m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{report_name}} / {{result}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Export job duration",
      "description": "graph2otel_export_duration_seconds{report_name,tenant_id}.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 42 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "s" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["lastNotNull"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_export_duration_seconds{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{report_name}} ({{tenant_id}})"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Export poll count",
      "description": "graph2otel_export_poll_count{report_name,tenant_id} — how many polls it took for the export job to complete; a rising trend indicates the export API is slow or throttled.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 42 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["lastNotNull"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_export_poll_count{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{report_name}} ({{tenant_id}})"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Active series (cardinality guard)",
      "description": "graph2otel_series_active{metric_name} vs graph2otel_series_limit — catches cardinality blowups before they hit the OTLP backend's series limit.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 49 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": { "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false },
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum(graph2otel_series_active{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"})",
          "legendFormat": "active series"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Overflowing series",
      "description": "graph2otel_series_overflowing — count of metric series that exceeded the cardinality guard and were dropped/capped. Should be 0.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 49 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              { "color": "green", "value": null },
              { "color": "red", "value": 1 }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": { "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false },
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum(graph2otel_series_overflowing{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"})",
          "legendFormat": "overflowing series"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Series limit",
      "description": "graph2otel_series_limit — the configured cardinality ceiling, for context against active/overflowing series.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 49 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": { "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false },
        "colorMode": "none",
        "graphMode": "none"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_series_limit{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "legendFormat": "limit"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Throttle & rate limiting",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 55 }
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Throttle (429) count by workload",
      "description": "graph2otel_throttle_count_total{workload,tenant_id} — 429 responses from Graph, broken down by which client-side rate-limiter workload was throttled (reporting, identity-protection, intune-export, directory).",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 56 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "short" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["sum"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "sum by (workload) (rate(graph2otel_throttle_count_total{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{workload}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Throttle limit usage by workload",
      "description": "graph2otel_throttle_limit_percentage{workload,tenant_id} — how close each workload's client-side rate limiter is running to its ceiling (%). Sustained values near 100% mean the limiter is actively shaping traffic, not just headroom.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 56 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "percent", "min": 0, "max": 100 },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["lastNotNull", "max"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "graph2otel_throttle_limit_percentage{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{workload}} ({{tenant_id}})"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Outbound Graph request latency (p95)",
      "description": "graph2otel_http_client_request_duration{tenant_id} histogram — p95 latency of outbound requests to Graph, via histogram_quantile. Rising latency alongside throttle count points at Graph-side throttling rather than a client bug.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 56 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": { "unit": "s" },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["lastNotNull"] },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "$datasource" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(graph2otel_http_client_request_duration_bucket{tenant_id=~\"$tenant\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
